\begin{enumerate}
\item Find the tile side length (cm).
\item Find the number of tiles needed.
\end{enumerate}

\item Ropes of length 2.1 m and 3.5 m are cut into equal pieces of greatest possible length (no leftover).
\begin{enumerate}
\item Find the length of each piece (cm).
\item Find the number of pieces from each rope.
\end{enumerate}

\item A hall has $N$ chairs. When arranged in rows of 6 or rows of 8, there are always 2 chairs left over. Find the least possible $N$.

\item Three buses arrive every 12 min, 18 min and 30 min. They arrive together at 07:40. Find the next time they arrive together.

\item Boxes of height 6 cm and 10 cm are stacked (separately) to the same height.
\begin{enumerate}
\item Find the minimum common height.
\item Find the number of 6 cm boxes and 10 cm boxes required.
\end{enumerate}

\item Ribbons of 90 cm, 120 cm and 150 cm are cut into equal pieces of greatest possible length (no leftover).
\begin{enumerate}
\item Find the length of each piece.
\item Find the number of pieces from each ribbon.
\end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}

